definitions.definition: To cast off or out (someone or something); to reject , especially as contemptible or inferior .
To cast down (someone or something); to abase ; to debase ; to degrade ; to lower ; also, to forcibly impose obedience or servitude upon (someone); to subjugate .
Of a fungus : to (forcibly) give off ( spores or sporidia ).

main_definition: To cast off or out (someone or something); to reject , especially as contemptible or inferior . [from 15th c.]
secondary_definitions: To cast down (someone or something); to abase ; to debase ; to degrade ; to lower ; also, to forcibly impose obedience or servitude upon (someone); to subjugate . [from 15th c.]
( mycology ) Of a fungus : to (forcibly) give off ( spores or sporidia ).
